<paragraph id="4A72C1394529350D2BB79E61FCC1F851" blockId="19.[151,1437,1511,2043]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
<bibRefCitation id="2E5CBCC84529350D2BB79E61FE03F888" author="Blackburn, T." box="[199,412,1800,1827]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" pagination="805 - 875" refId="ref24682" refString="Blackburn, T. (1888 b) Notes on Australian Coleoptera with descriptions of new species. Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales, Series 2, 3, 805 - 875." type="journal article" year="1888">Blackburn (1888b)</bibRefCitation>
saw three specimens that “appear[ed] to be of the same sex” but did not designate a ‘type’. 
<bibRefCitation id="2E5CBCC84529350D2BE79E44FE8CF8ED" author="Lea, A. M." box="[151,275,1836,1863]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refId="ref25947" refString="Lea, A. M. (1912) The late Rev. Canon Thomas Blackburn, B. A., and his entomological work. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Australia, 36, v-xl." type="book" year="1912">Lea (1912)</bibRefCitation>
catalogued the ‘type’ as in SAM, and 
<bibRefCitation id="2E5CBCC84529350D29B69E45FCF8F8ED" author="Britton, E. B." box="[710,871,1836,1862]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref25258" refString="Britton, E. B. (1978) A revision of the Australian chafers (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Vol. 2. Tribe Melolonthini. Australian Journal of Zoology, Supplementary Series, 60, 1 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / AJZS 060" type="journal article" year="1978">Britton (1978)</bibRefCitation>
referred to a “ 
<typeStatus id="95767F9B4529350D2F7A9E45FBEEF8ED" box="[1034,1137,1836,1862]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">holotype</typeStatus>
” male and two “ 
<typeStatus id="95767F9B4529350D2E5D9E45FA0CF8ED" box="[1325,1427,1836,1862]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">paratype</typeStatus>
” males in SAM all from the 
<collectingRegion id="88090FDB4529350D2ABB9E39FD03F8C1" box="[459,668,1872,1898]" country="Australia" name="Northern Territory" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">Northern Territory</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="2E5CBCC84529350D29D79E38FC2EF8C1" author="Houston, W. W. K. &amp; Weir, T. A." box="[679,945,1872,1899]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refId="ref25821" refString="Houston, W. W. K. &amp; Weir, T. A. (1992) Melolonthinae. In: Houston, W. W. K. (Ed.), Zoological Catalogue of Australia. Coleoptera: Scarabaeoidea. Vol. 9. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra, pp. 174 - 358." type="book" year="1992">Houston &amp; Weir (1992)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<bibRefCitation id="2E5CBCC84529350D2F499E39FB73F8C1" author="Britton, E. B." box="[1081,1260,1872,1898]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref25258" refString="Britton, E. B. (1978) A revision of the Australian chafers (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Vol. 2. Tribe Melolonthini. Australian Journal of Zoology, Supplementary Series, 60, 1 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / AJZS 060" type="journal article" year="1978">Britton’s (1978)</bibRefCitation>
incorrect reference to a 
<typeStatus id="95767F9B4529350D2A799E1DFEF4F825" box="[265,363,1908,1934]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">holotype</typeStatus>
as being a 
<typeStatus id="95767F9B4529350D2A829E1DFDC6F825" box="[498,601,1908,1934]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation. As 
<bibRefCitation id="2E5CBCC84529350D286B9E1DFC21F825" author="Britton, E. B." box="[795,958,1908,1934]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref25258" refString="Britton, E. B. (1978) A revision of the Australian chafers (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Vol. 2. Tribe Melolonthini. Australian Journal of Zoology, Supplementary Series, 60, 1 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / AJZS 060" type="journal article" year="1978">Britton (1978)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="2E5CBCC84529350D28899E1CFA95F825" author="Houston, W. W. K. &amp; Weir, T. A." box="[1017,1290,1908,1935]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refId="ref25821" refString="Houston, W. W. K. &amp; Weir, T. A. (1992) Melolonthinae. In: Houston, W. W. K. (Ed.), Zoological Catalogue of Australia. Coleoptera: Scarabaeoidea. Vol. 9. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra, pp. 174 - 358." type="book" year="1992">Houston &amp; Weir (1992)</bibRefCitation>
provided no discussion and did not label any specimen in SAM, neither mention of a 
<typeStatus id="95767F9B4529350D28B69EF1FBB7F819" box="[966,1064,1944,1970]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">holotype</typeStatus>
constitutes a valid 
<typeStatus id="95767F9B4529350D2E709EF1FAF8F819" box="[1280,1383,1944,1970]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation (vide Article 74.5). To stabilise nomenclature, I designate the specimen in SAM with the ‘TYPE’ label the 
<typeStatus id="95767F9B4529350D2BE79E89FE9EF851" box="[151,257,2016,2042]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The other two specimens in SAM are 
<typeStatus id="95767F9B4529350D29C59E89FCC5F851" box="[693,858,2016,2042]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
